Six people were killed on Saturday in an attack by raiders against Turkana herders at Buffalo Springs game reserve in Isiolo County. According to Isiolo County Commissioner Herman Shambi, attackers from the Samburu side tried to steal livestock from Turkana herders who resisted, and a gun battle ensued. Five attackers from the Samburu side and one Turkana herder were killed during the shootout. Shambi asked the various pastoralist communities in Isiolo County to respect each otherâ€™s grazing zones to avert further flare ups. Video Of The Day: CAS Rachel Shebesh and athlete Asbel Kiprop share their mental health journeys